{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566880","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566880"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:50:14+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:50:14+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18900"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18900","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18900"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.91,0.04,0.02,0.02,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11633"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80108"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11633","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11633"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18900"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65385"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"17"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11343"},{"type":"tags","id":"11346"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27367"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27368"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80108","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80108"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA junior doctor is supervising medical students during their clinical rotation. During ward rounds, one student consistently struggles to answer questions about patient management. The junior doctor notices that other staff members sometimes make dismissive comments when the student gives incorrect answers.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate approach for the junior doctor to support the student\u0027s learning?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Create opportunities for private discussion and structured feedback","Focus questions on topics the student answered correctly previously","Wait for the student to seek help independently","Tell the student to study harder before attending rounds","Request that the student be reassigned to a different team"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most appropriate approach is to \u003Cstrong\u003Ecreate opportunities for private discussion and structured feedback\u003C/strong\u003E. This allows for constructive dialogue about learning needs, helps maintain the student\u0027s dignity, and demonstrates commitment to supporting their development in a psychologically safe environment.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect approaches are problematic because:\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFocus questions on topics the student answered correctly previously\u003C/strong\u003E - This limits learning opportunities and does not address underlying knowledge gaps or confidence issues\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERequest that the student be reassigned to a different team\u003C/strong\u003E - This avoids addressing the problem and may further damage the student\u0027s confidence\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETell the student to study harder before attending rounds\u003C/strong\u003E - This is unhelpful, potentially demeaning feedback that does not provide specific guidance for improvement\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWait for the student to seek help independently\u003C/strong\u003E - This is a passive approach that fails to fulfil the supervisor\u0027s responsibility to support learning\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EEffective clinical teaching requires creating an environment where students feel safe to demonstrate their current level of knowledge, make mistakes, and ask questions. Supervisors should actively support learning while maintaining professional standards and respect.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Effective clinical teaching requires clear expectations, constructive feedback, and respect for learners\u0027 psychological safety.","Humiliation and aggressive questioning techniques harm learning and student wellbeing.","Creating a supportive learning environment involves encouraging questions and acknowledging uncertainty."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx","Hayden C, Raidan J, Rees J, Oswal A. Understanding junior doctors\u0027 experiences of teaching on the acute take: a qualitative study. BMC Med Educ. 2021 Jul 13;21(1):383. doi: 10.1186/s12909-021-02815-4. PMID: 34256755; PMCID: PMC8278645. Available from: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8278645/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65385"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18900"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65385","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65385"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-17T13:00:06+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-17T13:01:07+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11633"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80108"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"17","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/17"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude07","name":"Bioethics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1